<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1323,431,1057]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">
<materialsCitation collectionCode="T" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" specimenCode="T1, T4" specimenCount="2" specimenCount-female="1" specimenCount-male="1">
Differential diagnosis. 
<specimenCount box="[579,599,630,650]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[655,673,632,650]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
. Body mainly black. Head about as long as wide. Terga without apical hair bands. Marginal zone of 
<specimenCode box="[814,844,671,697]" collectionCode="T" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">T1</specimenCode>
­ 
<specimenCode box="[853,889,671,697]" collectionCode="T" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">T4</specimenCode>
with few appressed hair on lateral margins
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1323,431,1057]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">
Diagnosis (
<figureCitation box="[445,519,751,777]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[264,367,1610,1634]" captionTargetBox="[305,1292,1109,1590]" captionTargetId="figure-213@8.[299,1296,1105,1595]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Eremaphanta iranica, male (scale=300µm); a. Sternum 7; b. Sternum 8; c. Dorsal view of genitalia; from Schwammberger (1971)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5058063" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5058063/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). 
<specimenCount box="[541,561,750,770]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
. Unknown. 
<specimenCount box="[706,723,752,770]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
. Tb1­Tb3 and tarsi yellow; other parts of the body entirely black. Head nearly as long as wide. Antennae dorsally brownish, ventrally yellowish. Propodeal triangle dull and rugose. Disc of terga with short brown appressed hairs. Marginal zone of 
<collectionCode box="[558,578,871,897]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">T</collectionCode>
1­ 
<collectionCode box="[597,617,871,897]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">T</collectionCode>
4 with few appressed hair on lateral margins. Premarginal line of S1­S5 slightly emarginate or straight. S7­S8 and genitalia as figured by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schwammberger, K. - H." box="[264,548,951,977]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref10170" refString="Schwammberger, K. - H. (1971) Zwei neue Bienen-Arten aus dem Iran (Hymenoptera, Apoidea). Stuttgarter Beitrge zur Naturkunde, 225, 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1971">Schwammberger (1971)</bibRefCitation>
(
<figureCitation box="[564,637,951,977]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[264,367,1610,1634]" captionTargetBox="[305,1292,1109,1590]" captionTargetId="figure-213@8.[299,1296,1105,1595]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Eremaphanta iranica, male (scale=300µm); a. Sternum 7; b. Sternum 8; c. Dorsal view of genitalia; from Schwammberger (1971)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5058063" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5058063/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
